.TH RENAME-SIMPLE 1 "2026-05-07" "rename-simple 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rename-simple \- clean filenames to lowercase, ASCII-safe slugs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rename-simple
[OPTIONS] [\fIDIR\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rename-simple
renames files and/or directories in \fIDIR\fR (default: current directory)
by normalising accented characters, replacing spaces and special characters
with hyphens, and lowercasing everything.
.PP
The transformation pipeline is:
.IP 1. 4
Transliterate accented and non-ASCII characters to their ASCII equivalents
(e.g. é -> e, ß -> ss, Æ -> ae).
.IP 2. 4
Replace all remaining special characters with a hyphen (\fB\-\fR).
.IP 3. 4
Collapse consecutive hyphens into a single hyphen.
.IP 4. 4
Clean underscore/hyphen boundaries (\fI_-\fR and \fI-_\fR become \fI_\fR).
.IP 5. 4
Collapse consecutive underscores.
.IP 6. 4
Strip leading and trailing hyphens and underscores.
.PP
Compound extensions (\fI.tar.gz\fR, \fI.tar.bz2\fR, \fI.tar.xz\fR,
\fI.tar.zst\fR) are preserved. Hidden files (names starting with a dot) are
never modified.
.PP
By default the program produces no output on success. Use
\fB\-v\fR/\fB\-\-verbose\fR to display details.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-f
Rename files only (default: files and directories).
.TP
.B \-d
Rename directories only (default: files and directories).
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-recursive
Process subdirectories recursively.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Show details of each rename operation and a summary.
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-dry-run
Show what would be renamed without actually renaming any entry.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print a help message and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
All entries were renamed successfully (or no entries needed renaming).
.TP
1
An error occurred (invalid arguments, I/O error, etc.).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Rename files in the current directory
rename-simple
.TP
Rename files in a specific directory with verbose output
rename-simple \-v ~/Downloads
.TP
Preview what would be renamed without touching anything
rename-simple \-n \-v
.TP
Recursively rename only files (skip directories)
rename-simple \-f \-r
.TP
Rename directories only
rename-simple \-d
